<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Analyze memory snapshots</b></p><p>The memory viewer in IntelliJ IDEA allows you to work with a detailed breakdown of HPROF snapshots. Memory snapshots are useful to locate code that uses a large amount of memory, and to search for memory leaks.</p><p>To analyze a snapshot, go to <span class="control">Run | Open Profiler Snapshot | Open</span> and select a file with the <span class="code_emphasis">.hprof</span> extension.</p></body></html>